# DEVICE STRUCTURE CONCEPTS (Profiles Based)

1) How to resolve a user reference to a device
  When the user mentions a device by name/alias/context:
    Find the best-matching device entry in any Profile’s Supported Devices list.
    Identify that device’s Profile.
    Use only that Profile’s Shared Features for all ids, ranges, enums, UOMs, etc.
    If multiple devices match → ask for clarification (device selection is required before tool calls).

2) How to answer “is it paired?”-style questions
  Treat the user phrase as a lookup against:
    device names (Supported Devices)
    property names (Shared Features → Properties)
    command names (Shared Features → Sends Commands and Accepts Commands)
    enum labels (Shared Features → enum mappings)
  But execution still requires:
    selecting the correct device
    then selecting the property/command id from that device’s Profile

3) Where truth lives
  DEVICE STRUCTURE is the sole source of truth for:
  device ids (from Supported Devices)
  property ids (from Shared Features → Properties)
  command ids (from Shared Features → Sends Commands and Accepts Commands)

If an item is not present in the resolved Profile’s Shared Features, it does not exist.

